===Noun===
'''zero''' (''plural'' '''[[zeros]]''' ''or'' '''[[zeroes]]''')

# The [[cardinal number]] which denotes no quantity or amount at all.
#:''When you add '''zero''' to (or subtract'' zero ''from) any number, the result is the original number.''
# The [[numeral]] [[0]] as a symbol which represents the number zero.
#:''When she found none, she wrote down '''zero'''.''
# The [[digit]] 0, zero, in the [[decimal]], [[binary]], and all other [[base]] numbering systems.
#:''One million has six '''zeros'''.''
# A point on a scale at which numbering or measurement begins.
#:''The temperature outside is ten degrees above'' zero ''Fahrenheit.''
# Nothing, nought. 
#:''The business did not lose money, but its profit was '''zero'''.''
#{{slang}} A person of little or no importance.
#{{mathematics}} A value of a function’s [[independent variable]]s for which the function is equal to zero.
#:''x''<sup>2</sup> &minus; 1 has '''zeros''' at +1 ''and'' &minus;1
#{{mathematics}} The [[identity element]] of an [[additive]] [[group]], especially the one of a [[ring]].
# Setting of a [[firearm]]. (''See'' '''[[zero in]]''')

